364
00:22:24,905 --> 00:22:27,601
I can see here that you don't own your home.

365
00:22:28,042 --> 00:22:30,704
You have no stocks, no bonds, no investments.

366
00:22:30,911 --> 00:22:32,640
You have a little over $1,000 in savings.

367
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:34,247
But we got insurance.

368
00:22:34,381 --> 00:22:36,246
That may very well be. 

369
00:22:36,383 --> 00:22:38,408
You're going to have to check with your carrier.

370
00:22:38,552 --> 00:22:40,679
In the meantime, we're going to have to treat this as a cash account.

371
00:22:40,821 --> 00:22:41,947
What?

372
00:22:42,089 --> 00:22:43,078
How much does a transplant cost?

373
00:22:43,224 --> 00:22:44,589
Wait a minute. 

374
00:22:44,725 --> 00:22:46,659
How much does it cost?

375
00:22:47,728 --> 00:22:49,389
Transplant surgery, doctors' fees, 

376
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:52,124
postoperative care,immunosuppressant drugs...

377
00:22:52,266 --> 00:22:55,258
you're looking at a minimum of $250,000.

378
00:22:55,636 --> 00:22:58,696
If you opt for transplant surgery, 

379
00:22:58,839 --> 00:22:59,931
that is your choice,

380
00:23:00,074 --> 00:23:02,565
but the hospital maintains a very

381
00:23:02,710 --> 00:23:04,143
strict policy with regard to cash patients.

382
00:23:04,278 --> 00:23:07,179
We require down payment before we put

383
00:23:07,314 --> 00:23:08,906
a patient's name on a receivers' list.

384
00:23:09,350 --> 00:23:09,975
How much?

385
00:23:10,117 --> 00:23:11,084
What kind of down payment?

386
00:23:11,218 --> 00:23:12,310
30%...

387
00:23:12,586 --> 00:23:14,110
$75,000.

388
00:23:14,421 --> 00:23:16,412
$75,000...

389
00:23:18,993 --> 00:23:20,688
To put my son's name on a list.

390
00:23:20,828 --> 00:23:23,888
Our son is upstairs dying. All you can do is talk about money?

391
00:23:24,031 --> 00:23:26,329
It costs money to provide health care.

392
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:29,658
It's expensive for you, it's expensive for us.

393
00:23:29,803 --> 00:23:30,497
You're going to have to guarantee payment

394
00:23:30,638 --> 00:23:34,130
before I can put your son's name on the list.

395
00:23:37,411 --> 00:23:39,743
Mr and Mrs Archibald, please wait!

396
00:23:42,116 --> 00:23:43,708
If you people don't want to treat our son,

397
00:23:43,851 --> 00:23:45,216
we'll take him over to County Memorial.

398
00:23:45,352 --> 00:23:46,410
You don't want to do that.

399
00:23:46,553 --> 00:23:48,111
They have to treat him.

400
00:23:48,255 --> 00:23:49,222
Heart transplantation is

401
00:23:49,356 --> 00:23:52,450
always considered an elective procedure.

402
00:23:52,593 --> 00:23:54,584
You're in the right place.

403
00:23:54,728 --> 00:23:55,888
What are we supposed to do?

404
00:23:56,196 --> 00:23:57,823
Talk to your insurance company again.

405
00:23:57,965 --> 00:24:00,593
Check with our human resources department for medical assistance.

406
00:24:00,734 --> 00:24:01,496
There's money. 

407
00:24:01,635 --> 00:24:04,160
There's Children's State Services and Medicaid.

408
00:24:04,305 --> 00:24:06,466
You find a way to keep him here.

409
00:24:06,707 --> 00:24:08,538
You just don't take no for an answer.

410
00:24:10,878 --> 00:24:14,279
Your policy has changed, Mr Archibald.

411
00:24:15,616 --> 00:24:16,412
Changed to what?

412
00:24:17,251 --> 00:24:19,685
We've recently switched carriers

413
00:24:19,820 --> 00:24:21,287
from a PPO to an HMO.

414
00:24:21,422 --> 00:24:22,684
It's a less expensive policy.

415
00:24:22,823 --> 00:24:25,758
Unfortunately, there are some restrictions.

416
00:24:25,893 --> 00:24:27,121
What kind of restrictions?

417
00:24:27,261 --> 00:24:28,455
Here's how it works.

418
00:24:29,096 --> 00:24:32,031
Non-management part-time employees such as yourself

419
00:24:32,166 --> 00:24:35,693
