00:27:04,785 --> 00:27:05,410
No, what?

464
00:27:05,552 --> 00:27:07,349
No, you don't qualify.

465
00:27:07,788 --> 00:27:09,278
My son is dying, I'm broke.

466
00:27:09,423 --> 00:27:10,549
If I don't qualify, who the hell does?

467
00:27:10,691 --> 00:27:11,385
I'm sorry.

468
00:27:12,226 --> 00:27:14,558
I don't need you to be sorry! I need you to help me!

469
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:41,988
No, this is an appeal.

470
00:27:43,257 --> 00:27:45,555
An appeal is for an already existing claim.

471
00:27:45,692 --> 00:27:47,683
You needed to file a grievance.

472
00:27:47,828 --> 00:27:49,819
- You filed the wrong paperwork.
- Wait a minute.

473
00:27:50,164 --> 00:27:52,689
You're going to have to resubmit. It could take 30 days.

474
00:27:52,833 --> 00:27:53,857
I don't have 30 days.

475
00:27:54,001 --> 00:27:54,695
I know.

476
00:27:54,835 --> 00:27:56,462
I'm getting sick of the run-around.

477
00:27:56,603 --> 00:27:58,468
I need my son's name on that list.

478
00:27:58,605 --> 00:28:02,666
Your account is in excess of $30,000.

479
00:28:03,243 --> 00:28:05,575
The hospital has bent over backwards to help you out.

480
00:28:05,712 --> 00:28:06,303
Is that right?

481
00:28:06,446 --> 00:28:07,242
Yes, it is right.

482
00:28:07,381 --> 00:28:10,009
But there is a limit to our generosity.

483
00:28:10,817 --> 00:28:14,275
Once and for all, your insurance does not cover this.

484
00:28:34,241 --> 00:28:35,401
Take it.

