00:33:33,106 --> 00:33:34,038
You're doing great. You really are.

546
00:33:34,174 --> 00:33:36,335
You've gained what, five pounds?

547
00:33:37,244 --> 00:33:40,577
You're the only patient I have who eats the food in this place.

548
00:33:41,648 --> 00:33:42,842
Doc, let me ask you something.

549
00:33:42,983 --> 00:33:44,848
How long before I'm able to play tennis?

550
00:33:44,985 --> 00:33:46,919
You couldn't play before you had a new heart. 

551
00:33:47,053 --> 00:33:49,078
Take up knitting.

552
00:33:49,890 --> 00:33:50,754
I play tennis.

553
00:33:50,891 --> 00:33:52,017
We don't care.

554
00:33:52,158 --> 00:33:54,353
Would you please get back to work? Thank you.

555
00:33:54,694 --> 00:33:57,026
Heidi, make an appointment for us to have dinner next week.

556
00:33:57,163 --> 00:33:58,562
I'm going to cook.

557
00:33:58,698 --> 00:33:59,995
No,

558
00:34:00,133 --> 00:34:01,862
and you're not wearing lingerie around him the next month.

559
00:34:02,002 --> 00:34:03,867
You're not in his will. He told me.

560
00:34:04,004 --> 00:34:06,063
Don't push your luck.

561
00:34:06,373 --> 00:34:08,933
I gave the hospital $6,000 yesterday.

562
00:34:11,411 --> 00:34:12,673
Can I talk to you?

563
00:34:12,812 --> 00:34:14,245
Yes, sure.

564
00:34:18,418 --> 00:34:19,851
Take care of him.

565
00:34:19,986 --> 00:34:21,283
Take care. Thank you.

566
00:34:27,761 --> 00:34:30,662
My wife Denise says you're going to send Michael home. Is that true?

567
00:34:30,797 --> 00:34:32,992
I'm a physician. 

568
00:34:33,133 --> 00:34:34,657
I don't make policy decisions.

569
00:34:34,801 --> 00:34:36,325
That's handled by the board of trustees.

570
00:34:36,469 --> 00:34:37,959
You're the head of cardiac surgery.

571
00:34:38,104 --> 00:34:40,368
You make a recommendation, they're going to listen, aren't they?

572
00:34:40,507 --> 00:34:42,031
I make recommendations all the time.

573
00:34:42,175 --> 00:34:46,942
The final decision rests with the board. That's it? Send him home.

574
00:34:47,180 --> 00:34:48,511
I'm afraid so.

575
00:34:49,950 --> 00:34:52,646
Can we take a little walk?

576
00:34:52,919 --> 00:34:55,080
It won't take long, I promise you.

577
00:34:55,221 --> 00:34:56,153
Fine.

578
00:34:57,290 --> 00:35:00,225
I'm looking at the brochure last night.

579
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,660
It says this hospital

580
00:35:02,796 --> 00:35:04,855
does over 300 heart surgeries a year.

581
00:35:04,998 --> 00:35:06,431
300 surgeries,

582
00:35:06,566 --> 00:35:09,034
$250,000 a pop.You know how much that is? 

583
00:35:09,169 --> 00:35:10,363
I did the math.

584
00:35:10,503 --> 00:35:13,233
That's $75 million worth of heart surgeries.

585
00:35:13,373 --> 00:35:15,534
You're telling me 

586
00:35:15,675 --> 00:35:16,437
you can't do one for me in good faith?

587
00:35:16,576 --> 00:35:18,339
I waived my fee in your son's case.

588
00:35:18,478 --> 00:35:19,877
I know you're not asking...

589
00:35:20,013 --> 00:35:21,344
Nobody asked you to waive the fee.

590
00:35:21,481 --> 00:35:22,448
I can raise the money.

591
00:35:22,582 --> 00:35:26,040
I already came up with $22,000, 

592
00:35:26,186 --> 00:35:29,314
and I swear to God on my life, I will pay for this 

593
00:35:29,456 --> 00:35:30,787
if you give me the opportunity.

594
00:35:30,924 --> 00:35:33,358
I'm only getting 20 hours on the job.

595
00:35:33,493 --> 00:35:36,053
I can do this. I can pay. I swear to God,

596
00:35:36,196 --> 00:35:37,720
I'll pay you the money back.

597
00:35:37,864 --> 00:35:40,025
I don't know how, but I promise you I will.

598
00:35:40,166 --> 00:35:42,225
Trust me.

599
00:35:42,369 --> 00:35:44,894
I give you my word as a man. Please.

600
00:35:47,641 --> 00:35:50,109
Could you take your hands off me, please?

601
00:35:52,278 --> 00:35:53,870
I've done everything I can. I'm sorry.

602
00:35:54,014 --> 00:35:54,981
No, you haven't.

603
00:35:55,115 --> 00:35:56,082
Yes.

604
00:35:56,216 --> 00:35:57,774
Let's go inside and talk about it.

605
00:36:03,690 --> 00:36:05,988
I'm not asking anymore, Doctor. I'm telling you.

606
00:36:06,126 --> 00:36:09,061
You are going to give my son a new heart, you understand me?

607
00:36:18,271 --> 00:36:19,260
Don't move.

608
00:36:31,685 --> 00:36:33,243
Don't even think about it.

609
00:36:34,587 --> 00:36:36,020
Put your hands down.

610
00:36:37,323 --> 00:36:38,255
Mr Archibald, I...

611
00:36:38,391 --> 00:36:38,982
Shut up.

612
00:36:39,125 --> 00:36:41,685
I know how upset you are, but this is not the way to handle it.

613
00:36:42,562 --> 00:36:43,893
You can't go through this way.

614
00:36:44,731 --> 00:36:46,130
Put your hands up.

615
00:36:46,266 --> 00:36:48,700
- Put them up.
- Oh, God.

616
00:36:50,203 --> 00:36:51,170
Give me your gun.

617
00:36:51,304 --> 00:36:51,998
I don't have a gun.

618
00:36:52,138 --> 00:36:53,628
They don't have guns. They're not armed.

619
00:36:53,773 --> 00:36:55,172
All right. 

620
00:36:55,308 --> 00:36:57,572
Put your hands down. Sit down.

621
00:36:57,711 --> 00:36:58,735
No, get up.

622
00:36:58,878 --> 00:37:01,506
- You fail to realise the jeopardy...
- Get over here. Shut up!

623
00:37:01,648 --> 00:37:02,342
We have got to talk about this.

624
00:37:02,482 --> 00:37:03,949
Shut up. Don't move.

625
00:37:05,685 --> 00:37:06,947
John, wait.

626
00:37:07,087 --> 00:37:10,648
Just stop. Stop! If you do this, 

627
00:37:10,790 --> 00:37:12,781
you're on an irreversible course of action.

628
00:37:12,926 --> 00:37:14,791
Put on the brakes
and think about this.

629
00:37:14,928 --> 00:37:16,088
- We really need to talk.
- Mr Archibald, I hope...

630
00:37:17,630 --> 00:37:18,562
- Back up, please.
- What?

631
00:37:19,532 --> 00:37:20,226
Do as he says.

632
00:37:20,366 --> 00:37:21,196
Would you please back up?

633
00:37:21,334 --> 00:37:22,164
What are you doing?

634
00:37:24,104 --> 00:37:25,833
I'm not taking no for an answer.

635
00:37:25,972 --> 00:37:27,132
- Back up.
- That guy's got a gun!

636
00:37:29,168 --> 00:37:30,449
Stay right there.

637
00:37:36,950 --> 00:37:38,281
What are you doing? Get back over there.

638
00:37:38,418 --> 00:37:41,615
Sit on your hands over there!

639
00:37:42,355 --> 00:37:43,447
Get over there!

640
00:37:43,590 --> 00:37:44,955
Turner, everybody, get down!

641
00:37:46,292 --> 00:37:47,554
Sit on your hands!

642
00:37:48,027 --> 00:37:49,619
Put your hands under your butt!

643
00:37:50,230 --> 00:37:51,390
Don't anybody move.

644
00:37:57,303 --> 00:37:58,497
What are you doing?

645
00:37:59,372 --> 00:38:03,399
I'm bleeding. Trying to get my goddamned finger sewn back on.

646
00:38:04,244 --> 00:38:07,179
Mr Archibald, these people have nothing to do with this.

647
00:38:07,313 --> 00:38:10,043
Let them go. They need treatment.

648
00:38:10,183 --> 00:38:13,778
This is a hospital. You're a doctor. Why don't you treat them? Start with him.

649
00:38:14,888 --> 00:38:16,150
What's the matter, Doctor?

650
00:38:16,623 --> 00:38:18,921
You want to see his insurance card first?

651
00:38:20,026 --> 00:38:20,993
I'll do it.

652
00:38:21,561 --> 00:38:22,721
Okay, you do it.

653
00:38:23,196 --> 00:38:25,721
Wait a minute. I got a pregnant wife here.

654
00:38:29,002 --> 00:38:31,300
Listen, all right, wait. Listen, everybody.

655
00:38:33,740 --> 00:38:36,903
The hospital's under new management now.

656
00:38:39,078 --> 00:38:42,172
From now on, free health care for everybody. How's that?

657
00:38:42,315 --> 00:38:43,441
Righteous, man.

658
00:38:43,583 --> 00:38:46,643
Don't have to squeeze it like... You crazy?

659
00:38:46,953 --> 00:38:48,045
What's your name?

660
00:38:48,188 --> 00:38:48,654
Max.

661
00:38:48,788 --> 00:38:50,983
You and Dr Turner come with me.

662
00:38:52,725 --> 00:38:53,919
- You got keys for that elevator?
- Yeah.

663
00:38:54,060 --> 00:38:56,893
I want you to kill the power. Turn it off.

664
00:39:17,250 --> 00:39:18,945
- Keep an eye on him, Max.
- 

665
00:39:19,652 --> 00:39:21,813
You got to sit still. I can't do this with you moving around.

666
00:39:21,955 --> 00:39:23,786
You remind me of Doogie Howser.

667
00:39:25,191 --> 00:39:27,182
We were here before the black guy.

668
00:39:27,627 --> 00:39:28,821
Everybody's going to get their turn.

669
00:39:28,962 --> 00:39:31,362
We're not going anywhere for a while, so just sit tight.

670
00:39:32,899 --> 00:39:34,799
Just relax, okay?

671
00:39:47,580 --> 00:39:49,514
Is this Hope Memorial Hospital?

672
00:39:49,782 --> 00:39:51,613
Yeah, emergency room.

673
00:39:51,751 --> 00:39:54,447
Could you give me directions? I need to get over there.

674
00:39:54,587 --> 00:39:55,212
No, ma'am.

675
00:39:58,725 --> 00:40:00,693
We're closed for repairs right now. You're going to have to call...

676
00:40:00,827 --> 00:40:02,192
This is an emergency!

677
00:40:04,664 --> 00:40:06,427
Have you tried Mount Angel?

678
00:40:06,566 --> 00:40:08,261
No. That's too far. 

679
00:40:08,401 --> 00:40:10,460
My husband usually drives.

680
00:40:10,603 --> 00:40:12,468
I'm going to need directions.

681
00:40:12,605 --> 00:40:13,731
Which way are you coming from?

682
00:40:14,841 --> 00:40:17,071
Go down Flower, make a right turn,

683
00:40:17,210 --> 00:40:19,542
go all the way to the end, make a left. You understand?

684
00:40:19,679 --> 00:40:21,237
I'm asking you to do something.

685
00:40:21,381 --> 00:40:23,679
You're welcome. Miss, come from under there.

686
00:40:27,353 --> 00:40:29,287
Come from out of there. Come on out.

687
00:40:29,388 --> 00:40:31,297
What? No, what?

688
00:40:32,525 --> 00:40:33,719
Go sit over there.

689
00:40:35,695 --> 00:40:38,459
Unbelievable. This place is a joke.

690
00:40:38,932 --> 00:40:40,024
Good thing I'm not cut.

691
00:40:40,166 --> 00:40:42,498
I'd bleed to death in this joint, am I right?

692
00:40:43,136 --> 00:40:44,160
Excuse me, brother man!

693
00:40:45,638 --> 00:40:48,573
No. You need to do something, Steve, all right?

694
00:40:48,708 --> 00:40:50,903
You need to get your butt up!

695
00:40:51,044 --> 00:40:52,409
I want you to do something.

696
00:40:52,545 --> 00:40:53,375
Would you please sit down?

697
00:40:53,513 --> 00:40:54,445
I don't want to sit down!

698
00:40:54,580 --> 00:40:55,877
What is wrong with you?

699
00:40:56,015 --> 00:40:59,644
Wait a minute.

700
00:40:59,786 --> 00:41:01,253
Relax. Don't have the baby yet.

701
00:41:01,387 --> 00:41:01,944
When is it due?

702
00:41:02,088 --> 00:41:02,747
Any minute.

703
00:41:02,889 --> 00:41:04,447
Don't have it.

704
00:41:04,590 --> 00:41:05,420
I'm having it.

705
00:41:05,558 --> 00:41:06,650
Not yet. Hang on.

706
00:41:06,793 --> 00:41:07,623
Brother.

707
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:09,523
She's having a baby. Hang on a second.

708
00:41:09,662 --> 00:41:11,630
Excuse me, brother man.

709
00:41:11,764 --> 00:41:13,732
The woman's having a baby!

710
00:41:13,866 --> 00:41:14,992
When is she going to see a doctor?

711
00:41:15,134 --> 00:41:15,998
Sit down!

712
00:41:17,403 --> 00:41:18,165
Sit down!

713
00:41:18,304 --> 00:41:18,998
That's cool.

714
00:41:19,138 --> 00:41:20,196
Dr Klein!

715
00:41:20,340 --> 00:41:21,705
I'll be there in a minute.

716
00:41:21,841 --> 00:41:23,741
You and me, we got no problems.

717
00:41:23,876 --> 00:41:28,973
That's right. Just stay in your seat.

718
00:41:31,317 --> 00:41:33,717
I don't understand what you're saying, ma'am.

719
00:41:36,155 --> 00:41:38,919
The ear? Ear infection?

720
00:41:39,592 --> 00:41:40,957
Can you help her with the ear infection?

721
00:41:41,094 --> 00:41:41,753
Me? 

722
00:41:42,795 --> 00:41:43,625
I can't.

723
00:41:43,763 --> 00:41:44,787
Why not?

724
00:41:45,064 --> 00:41:47,624
I don't know anything. It's my first day.

725
00:41:58,111 --> 00:41:59,806
Everybody, in the other room.

726
00:42:00,413 --> 00:42:03,007
Everybody, in the other room right now.

727
00:42:04,283 --> 00:42:06,410
They're going to take great care of you, I promise.

728
00:42:06,886 --> 00:42:08,444
What? Open up!

729
00:42:09,389 --> 00:42:10,413
It's dropping.

730
00:42:11,057 --> 00:42:12,547
We've got a gunshot victim out here.

731
00:42:12,692 --> 00:42:13,784
He's lost a lot of blood.

732
00:42:14,994 --> 00:42:16,894
Go to another hospital.

733
00:42:17,263 --> 00:42:18,491
Let's go. Open the door.

734
00:42:19,198 --> 00:42:19,960
You know these guys?

735
00:42:21,401 --> 00:42:22,265
You sure?

736
00:42:22,402 --> 00:42:23,596
They're here all the time.

737
00:42:23,936 --> 00:42:24,800
Open the door.

738
00:42:28,674 --> 00:42:29,538
Take your jacket off.

739
00:42:29,675 --> 00:42:30,369
What?

740
00:42:32,011 --> 00:42:34,309
Open it up. Take it off.

741
00:42:35,415 --> 00:42:38,111
Put it on the ground. Walk away.

742
00:42:38,251 --> 00:42:40,082
Just leave him right there. Go!

743
00:42:41,587 --> 00:42:42,645
Just go.

744
00:42:45,792 --> 00:42:46,724
What's wrong with him?

745
00:42:47,660 --> 00:42:48,752
He got shot.

746
00:42:55,243 --> 00:42:56,869
All right, come on.

747
00:43:08,181 --> 00:43:11,514
Wait a minute. I want to see what's in that bag.

748
00:43:13,553 --> 00:43:17,080
I gave them all the money in the register.

749
00:43:17,690 --> 00:43:19,555
They shot me anyway.

750
00:43:19,692 --> 00:43:21,182
Jesus Christ.

751
00:43:21,561 --> 00:43:23,859
He needs to go into surgery right now.

752
00:43:23,996 --> 00:43:24,519
Can I take him to Trauma One?

753
00:43:24,664 --> 00:43:25,528
Thanks.

754
00:43:26,232 --> 00:43:27,290
What do we got?

755
00:43:27,433 --> 00:43:28,525
Gunshot wound to the belly.

756
00:43:28,901 --> 00:43:29,959
Anything from the EMTs?

757
00:43:30,103 --> 00:43:30,569
No. 

758
00:43:30,703 --> 00:43:32,261
Dr Turner, we're going to need your hand.

759
00:43:32,405 --> 00:43:33,372
I just bought this suit.

760
00:43:35,975 --> 00:43:36,771
Can you give me a hand?

761
00:43:36,909 --> 00:43:39,400
On three, two, one, lift.

762
00:43:39,679 --> 00:43:40,270
Thank you.

763
00:43:42,882 --> 00:43:44,474
I can't handle a gut shot.

764
00:43:44,617 --> 00:43:46,812
I'm a cardiac surgeon, not an emergency room physician.

765
00:43:46,953 --> 00:43:48,978
It's like riding a bike, Doctor.

766
00:43:49,122 --> 00:43:50,453
Just pretend you're getting paid.

767
00:43:51,090 --> 00:43:53,024
This is apples and oranges. I can't.

768
00:43:53,159 --> 00:43:54,490
The man is dying. Help him.

769
00:43:54,627 --> 00:43:55,491
I'd like to. I haven't done this...

770
00:43:55,628 --> 00:43:56,686
Do it!

771
00:43:59,265 --> 00:44:01,165
75 milligrams Demerol I.V., lidocaine 2% local.

772
00:44:01,300 --> 00:44:02,232
I'll scrub now.

773
00:44:04,370 --> 00:44:07,498
When I get out of here, I'm suing this hospital and your security company.

774
00:44:07,640 --> 00:44:09,870
What makes you so sure you're getting out at all?

775
00:44:21,455 --> 00:44:22,450
Right behind you!

776
00:44:22,889 --> 00:44:23,947
Here we go.

777
00:44:38,538 --> 00:44:39,971
You've got to stand behind the line, sir.

778
00:44:40,439 --> 00:44:44,170
Move this out of here for me, please? Thank you very much.

779
00:44:44,810 --> 00:44:47,404
Lieutenant, we got a real problem here.

780
00:44:47,547 --> 00:44:48,070
What's that?

781
00:44:48,214 --> 00:44:49,772
This guy's in for the long haul...

782
00:44:49,916 --> 00:44:51,178
locked down the E.R.,

783
00:44:51,317 --> 00:44:54,411
barricaded himself in, killed power in the elevators.

784
00:44:54,554 --> 00:44:57,546
We can bust down the door, but this son of a bitch might start killing people.

785
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:00,124
There's two pinpoint cameras hidden in the E.R.

786
00:45:00,259 --> 00:45:02,159
The hospital's own surveillance.

787
00:45:02,295 --> 00:45:03,421
We got a video tap being set up.

788
00:45:03,563 --> 00:45:04,495
Are you in charge of security?

789
00:45:04,630 --> 00:45:07,724
No, that would be Wally Pitoniak. He's at home. It's his day off.

790
00:45:07,867 --> 00:45:10,267
Not anymore, it ain't. Get him here.

791
00:45:13,439 --> 00:45:14,565
All right, can you get me a secure line?

792
00:45:15,241 --> 00:45:17,368
We've got one of our guys inside. He's got a walkie-talkie.

793
00:45:17,510 --> 00:45:19,774
You might want to try this.

794
00:45:20,479 --> 00:45:22,811
Put a clamp on all phone lines to the emergency room.

795
00:45:22,949 --> 00:45:25,383
If this guy picks up the phone, I want him talking to me.

796
00:45:25,518 --> 00:45:26,644
Done.

797
00:45:28,020 --> 00:45:28,918
Who's in charge here?

798
00:45:29,055 --> 00:45:30,352
Rebecca Payne, sir.

799
00:45:30,623 --> 00:45:31,920
It's her day off, too.

800
00:45:32,058 --> 00:45:34,754
Jesus Christ, does anybody work at this hospital?

801
00:45:35,027 --> 00:45:36,051
It's Saturday, sir.

802
00:45:36,195 --> 00:45:37,184
So what?

803
00:45:37,863 --> 00:45:40,093
People get sick on Saturday, don't they?

804
00:45:46,739 --> 00:45:47,706
Ser, no cry.

805
00:45:52,411 --> 00:45:55,312
Mr Archibald, I need to do an internal examination on her.

806
00:45:55,548 --> 00:45:56,606
Where you going to take her?

807
00:45:56,816 --> 00:45:57,942
Examination room there.

808
00:45:58,150 --> 00:45:59,412
Good. Go.

809
00:46:07,727 --> 00:46:09,490
Just remember, it ain't your fault.

810
00:46:09,629 --> 00:46:10,561
Excuse me.

811
00:46:14,533 --> 00:46:16,728
I was wondering if we could get somebody to look at her.

812
00:46:16,869 --> 00:46:18,029
