01:04:04,402 --> 01:04:07,132
I feel good. We're having a baby!

1208
01:04:07,272 --> 01:04:10,105
Ma'am, any comments about the gunman?

1209
01:04:10,241 --> 01:04:12,368
John Q very good man.

1210
01:04:12,510 --> 01:04:13,499
The gunman?

1211
01:04:13,645 --> 01:04:15,613
Very good man!

1212
01:04:25,657 --> 01:04:26,453
They got a camera.

1213
01:04:26,591 --> 01:04:28,286
They're watching a video feed.

1214
01:04:28,426 --> 01:04:29,051
How do you know?

1215
01:04:29,194 --> 01:04:31,458
They're looking at something.

1216
01:04:31,596 --> 01:04:32,426
I want to know what. Can you get it?

1217
01:04:32,564 --> 01:04:35,089
Boss, if they got it, I can get it.

1218
01:04:35,433 --> 01:04:38,334
You give in, there's going to be guns in every hospital in the country.

1219
01:04:38,636 --> 01:04:41,434
You think Mr Archibald's the only one who has a sick child?

1220
01:04:41,573 --> 01:04:44,269
Have you checked the HIV ward? There's a whole floor full.

1221
01:04:44,776 --> 01:04:47,768
People get sick. They die. That's the way it goes.

1222
01:04:47,912 --> 01:04:50,142
I'm faced with decisions like this every day.

1223
01:04:50,281 --> 01:04:52,841
There's a man threatening innocent people 

1224
01:04:52,984 --> 01:04:54,884
because you refused to help his son.

1225
01:04:55,019 --> 01:04:59,217
There are 50 million people in this country 

1226
01:04:59,491 --> 01:05:00,651
without medical insurance.

1227
01:05:00,792 --> 01:05:02,191
If you'd like to change it, call your congressman.

1228
01:05:02,327 --> 01:05:03,157
Excuse me. 

1229
01:05:03,828 --> 01:05:06,296
Why don't we just tell him his son's name's on the list?

1230
01:05:06,431 --> 01:05:07,921
Doesn't that make sense?

1231
01:05:09,134 --> 01:05:10,726
How's he going to know, anyway?

1232
01:05:13,171 --> 01:05:16,607
Sir? Pardon me. Can you come take a look at this?

1233
01:05:20,812 --> 01:05:23,076
Sarge, Chief Moroe, this is Wally Pitoniak, head of security.

1234
01:05:23,848 --> 01:05:24,439
Nice to meet you.

1235
01:05:24,582 --> 01:05:26,049
I got your spot.

1236
01:05:26,584 --> 01:05:27,778
Here's your sight.

1237
01:05:28,520 --> 01:05:31,751
That's going to be your perch.

1238
01:05:32,223 --> 01:05:33,349
The X there, that's your phone.

1239
01:05:34,526 --> 01:05:35,356
Which phone?

1240
01:05:35,493 --> 01:05:36,425
Bring it up, Jeff.

1241
01:05:39,864 --> 01:05:41,456
The phone right there.

1242
01:05:45,336 --> 01:05:48,203
It is. Tom. But Chief Moroe maintains the police will do whatever is necessary

1243
01:05:48,339 --> 01:05:51,414
to preserve the lives and safety of these hostages.

1244
01:05:51,514 --> 01:05:52,143
Thanks. Tuck.

1245
01:05:52,243 --> 01:05:53,232
This country, man.

1246
01:05:53,378 --> 01:05:55,175
Can't go anywhere anymore without

1247
01:05:55,313 --> 01:05:58,840
getting mugged or murdered or stabbed.

1248
01:05:58,983 --> 01:06:01,281
Kids killing their classmates. Drive-bys.

1249
01:06:01,419 --> 01:06:03,853
I won't even go into a post office.

1250
01:06:03,988 --> 01:06:05,216
Shut up, Mitch.

1251
01:06:05,356 --> 01:06:06,323
You shut up.

1252
01:06:06,624 --> 01:06:08,319
I hate the little bastard, but he's right.

